            {
                "s2_paper_id": "b01cd0474fab48b1d3d4b3f8311c5b876827820b",
                "title": "Gravitational constant of Electron",
                "year": 2021,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 6,
                "abstract": "In this paper, the unique relationship between Gravitational and Electrostatic attraction is comprehended which provide us reason and derivation of known modern physics of charged sub-atomic particle and its problem using Newtonian Mechanics. Here, the Plasma frequency of cold electron is used for deriving the attraction constant for charged\u2013mass objects in terms of gravitational constant i.e. and by setting the value obtained result in Newton\u2019s gravitational formula it gives us Coulomb\u2019s force. The equation for charged particles placed at a certain distance with some conditions. Furthermore, a short derivation of the classical radius of electron and Bohr\u2019s Radius is shown by using the obtained attraction constant with the justifications.",
